    {
      "content": "Partition Selector",
      "pos": [
        12478,
        12496
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "PartitionSelector is a helper exposed in Testability and is used to select a specific partition on which to perform any of the Testability actions.",
      "pos": [
        12497,
        12644
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It can be used to select a specific partition if the partition ID is known beforehand.",
      "pos": [
        12645,
        12731
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Or, you can provide the partition key and the operation will resolve the partition ID internally.",
      "pos": [
        12732,
        12829
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You also have the option of selecting a random partition.",
      "pos": [
        12830,
        12887
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To use, create the PartitionSelector object and select the partition using one of the Select* methods and then pass in the PartitionSelector object to the API that requires it.",
      "pos": [
        12889,
        13065
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If no option is selected it defaults to random partition.",
      "pos": [
        13066,
        13123
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Replica Selector",
      "pos": [
        13936,
        13952
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "ReplicaSelector is a helper exposed in Testability and is used to help select a replica on which to perform any of the Testability actions.",
      "pos": [
        13953,
        14092
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It can be used to select a specific replica if the replica id is known beforehand.",
      "pos": [
        14093,
        14175
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In addition, you have the option of selecting a primary replica or a random secondary as well.",
      "pos": [
        14176,
        14270
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "ReplicaSelector derives from PartitionSelector, so you need to select both the replica and the partition on which you wish to perform the Testability operation.",
      "pos": [
        14271,
        14431
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To use, create a ReplicaSelector object and set the way you want to select the replica and the partition.",
      "pos": [
        14433,
        14538
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can then pass it into the API that requires it.",
      "pos": [
        14539,
        14590
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If no option is selected it defaults to random replica and random partition.",
      "pos": [
        14591,
        14667
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Guid partitionIdGuid = new Guid(\"8fb7ebcc-56ee-4862-9cc0-7c6421e68829\");",
      "pos": [
        14669,
        14741
      ]
    },
    {
